    answerText: "*Usually, no hard pull just to check options/pre-qualify.*\n\n*Public baseline:*\n• 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/integrations/other/acorn-finance|Acorn Finance> says Acorn uses a *soft credit check* and customers can get pre-qualified *without affecting their credit score*.\n\n*Internal context adds:*\n• 📕 Internal: <https://fieldpulse.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/FKB/pages/363954182|Wisetack Consumer Financing> explicitly says *“Checking Options Does Not Impact Credit Score”* — so for *Wisetack*, checking financing options is also *not* a hard pull.\n• 📕 Internal: <https://fieldpulse.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/FKB/pages/740098060|Acorn Finance> does *not* directly restate soft vs. hard pull, but it does say lender underwriting and credit score are factors, and lender-specific criteria apply.\n\n*Best internal answer to give:*\n• *Checking financing options / pre-qualification does not cause a hard pull* for both financing experiences we document:\n  • *Acorn*: soft pull per help center\n  • *Wisetack*: “checking options does not impact credit score” per internal doc\n• *Final approval / funded loan terms are still subject to lender credit approval and underwriting.* That means the *full application* may involve lender-specific credit review even though the initial check/pre-qual does not.\n\n*Important nuance / doc gap:*\n• Help center is clear for *Acorn*.\n• Internal docs are clear for *Wisetack*.\n• Internal Acorn docs talk about underwriting but *don’t explicitly confirm what happens later in the application flow*. So if someone asks, “Will the full loan application ever trigger a hard inquiry?” we *don’t have a definitive doc-backed answer here*.\n\n*Customer-safe phrasing:*\n• “You can check financing options without impacting your credit score.”\n• If they ask about post-prequal underwriting: “Final loan approval is handled by the lender and subject to credit approval.”\n\nIf useful, I can also give you the *exact customer-facing wording* to use for Acorn vs. Wisetack.",
