    questionText: "are there any limitation to pipline customer record statues a custstomer would like to see 22",
    threadContext: null,
    answerText: "I *still don’t see a documented hard platform limit* in the public docs for how many *Custom Sales Pipeline statuses* a company can create, so *22 statuses does not appear to be blocked by documented product limits*.\n\nPublic baseline:\n- You can *add, edit, delete, and reorder* pipeline statuses in *Company Settings > Customers > Pipeline Status*\n- Status names must be *unique per company*\n- New accounts get *7 default statuses*: *New, Contact Attempted, Contact Made, Scheduled, Estimate Sent, Won, Lost*\n- Source: 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/custom-sales-pipeline/custom-sales-pipeline|Custom Sales Pipeline>\n\nInternal context that *does* matter:\n- If the customer uses the *Marketing 360 integration*, there’s a practical limitation: *statuses only sync if matching values exist in both systems*. So even if FieldPulse allows 22 statuses, they *won’t all sync automatically* unless those same options are created in Marketing 360 too.\n  - 📕 Internal: <https://fieldpulse.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/FKB/pages/395542583|Integration Details: FieldPulse with Marketing 360 CRM>\n- That same doc says *Customer Pipeline Status in FieldPulse maps to Contact Statuses in Marketing 360*, and if matching values don’t exist, *the value will not sync*.\n- It also lists example customer status values seen in that integration context: *Lead, Opportunity, Current Customer, Lost Other, Inactive*. That is *not presented as a FieldPulse platform max*—just the values documented for that integration setup.\n- Additional internal evidence suggests statuses may be tied to mirrored *text/picklist fields* in automation flows, so *very custom status sets can have downstream automation dependencies* if the account has custom flows/integrations.\n  - 📕 Internal: <https://fieldpulse.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/FKB/pages/830898481|Lead Flows>\n\nSo the internal answer is:\n- *No documented FieldPulse product limit found* preventing *22 pipeline statuses*\n- *But* if they have *Marketing 360 or status-based automations*, the real limitation is *configuration/sync parity*, not the UI itself\n\nIf this is for a *plain FieldPulse account with no integration dependency*, I’d stand by: *22 should be fine based on current docs*.",
