    asker: { name: "Marcus Thorne", slackId: "U1003" },
    questionText: "If I send an email automatic trigger for an invoice will it show up in the internal activity of the invoice record?",
    threadContext: null,
    answerText: "I still *don’t see documentation that explicitly confirms* whether an invoice email sent by an *automatic trigger* shows in the invoice record’s *Internal Activity*.\n\nWhat we *can* say from docs:\n- 📘 Help Center: [Internal Activity](https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/internal-activity/internal-activity) says Internal Activity shows updates made by team members in FieldPulse.\n- 📘 Help Center: [Creating Automatic Triggers](https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/customers/communications/index) and [Sending Estimates & Invoices to Customers](https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/invoices-estimates/sending-estimates-invoices-to-customers) confirm invoice emails *can* be sent automatically.\n- *But neither source says those automated sends are logged on the invoice’s Internal Activity feed.*\n\nUseful internal context:\n- 📕 Internal: [Automatic Triggers Related to Invoices](https://fieldpulse.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/FKB/pages/884998173) gives trigger behavior details, but *still does not mention Internal Activity logging*.\n- That page does clarify the invoice trigger options:\n  - *When the invoice is past due* = old version, *no invoice link*.\n  - *When invoice is overdue and not yet fully paid (with Dynamic Invoice Link)* = sends when past due for *Invoiced* and *Partially Paid* invoices.\n  - *When invoice is sent and not yet paid (with Dynamic Invoice Link)* = internal doc says this *also sends on the date the invoice is past due* and only for *Invoiced* status.\n\nImportant nuance:\n- The internal doc labels the first option as an *old version* and says best practice is to use options *2 and 3*.\n- There’s also a wording oddity in option 3: the trigger name sounds like “sent and unpaid,” but the internal doc says it fires *on the date the invoice is past due*. That’s worth keeping in mind if testing behavior.\n\nSo the direct answer is:\n- *Not documented.* We cannot confidently tell a customer or teammate that auto-triggered invoice emails *will* appear in Internal Activity based on current docs.\n\nIf you need a definitive answer for a customer, this is one to *verify in product or with Support/Engineering*, because neither Help Center nor Confluence confirms the logging behavior.",
