    asker: { name: "Priya Patel", slackId: "U1004" },
    questionText: "if you void an invoice what happens in Quickbooks",
    threadContext: null,
    answerText: "I couldn’t find any relevant Confluence pages, so *the help center answer stands as-is*.\n\n*What we can say from FieldPulse docs:*\n* For *QuickBooks Online inventory-related invoices*, a void can be *blocked* if the transaction was created *before quantity-on-hand tracking started* for that inventory item.\n* The QuickBooks error is: *“You can’t delete or void this transaction because it was created before you started tracking quantity on hand…”*\n* Fix: update the *inventory tracking start date* in QuickBooks Online to a date *before the invoice date*, or make sure the invoice date is *after* the inventory tracking start date.\n* FieldPulse docs also note that if records are *deleted/archived in FieldPulse*, they are also *deleted in QuickBooks*.\n\n*What we do not have in FP docs:*\n* A general statement of the *accounting impact in QuickBooks* when an invoice is voided (for example, whether it becomes a zeroed transaction, how A/R is affected, etc.).\n\n*Sources:*\n* 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/invoices-estimates/how-do-i-sync-my-invoices-and-payments-to-quickbooks|How do I sync my invoices and payments to QuickBooks?>\n* 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/accounting/quickbooks-online/post-sync-quickbooks-online|Post-Sync: QuickBooks Online>\n* 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/accounting/quickbooks-desktop/post-sync-quickbooks-desktop|Post-Sync: QuickBooks Desktop>\n* 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/accounting/quickbooks-online/quickbooks-online-errors|QuickBooks Online Errors>\n* 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/accounting/quickbooks-desktop/quickbooks-desktop-errors|QuickBooks Desktop Errors>\n\nIf the rep/customer is asking about *QuickBooks’ accounting behavior specifically*, we *don’t currently have an internal FP doc covering that*.",
