    answerText: "I still *don’t see documentation that definitively says archived estimates are included in reporting*.\n\n*What’s confirmed publicly:*\n- The reporting docs cover estimate report types, filters, columns, and date ranges, but *do not mention archived estimates being included or excluded*.\n- So the Help Center baseline is still: *not documented*.\n  - 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/reporting/estimate-reports|Estimate Reports>\n  - 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/invoices-estimates/estimates-invoices|Estimates & Invoices>\n\n*What internal docs add:*\n- Internal reporting guidance lists the estimate-related reports available, including *Estimates by Status*, *Accepted Estimates*, *Estimate Follow-up*, etc.\n- That *suggests* archived estimates would only appear if the archive action preserves them in the underlying report dataset/status logic — but the internal doc still *does not explicitly confirm inclusion or exclusion*.\n  - 📕 Internal: <https://fieldpulse.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/FKB/pages/925433866|Reporting Use Cases for CS & Sales>\n\n*Best internal answer:*\n- *Not documented either way.*\n- If a customer asks, don’t state that archived estimates are included or excluded as fact.\n- The most likely place to validate behavior is *Estimates by Status* or *Number of Estimates Created*, but that’s an inference from internal docs, not a documented rule.\n\n*Net:*\n- Confluence adds *report names/use cases*, but *no definitive archived-estimate behavior*.\n- So I’d stand by the original answer: *we do not currently have doc-backed confirmation that archived estimates show up in reporting.*",
