    asker: { name: "Carlos Mendez", slackId: "U1021" },
    questionText: "best way to add \"asset worked on\" to a customer invoice?",
    threadContext: null,
    answerText: "I didn’t find any relevant Confluence pages, so *the help center answer still stands*.\n\n*Best documented option:* use *Assets* on the *job* and/or send an *Asset Report* with the invoice.\n\n*What the docs show:*\n- You can *attach an asset to a job* by editing the job and using *Select Asset* or *Add Asset*. 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/assets/assets|Assets>\n- When you create an invoice *from the job record*, the *customer and linked job* auto-populate. 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/invoices-estimates/creating-an-invoice|Creating an Invoice>\n- FieldPulse also says *Dynamic Asset Reports* can be shared with customers and *linked to dynamic estimates/invoices*. 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/assets/assets|Dynamic Asset Reports>\n\n*Recommended workflow:*\n- Enable *Assets* if needed.\n- Open the *Job Record* for the work performed.\n- Attach the correct asset using *Select Asset* or *Add Asset*.\n- Create the invoice from *Actions > Create Invoice* on that job. 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/invoices-estimates/creating-an-invoice|Creating an Invoice>\n- If the customer needs to clearly see which equipment/asset was serviced, generate and send an *Asset Report* with the invoice. 📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/assets/assets|Assets>\n\n*Important note:* I still couldn’t find documentation for a dedicated invoice field called *“asset worked on”* that prints directly on the invoice. If the ask is specifically to show that as a printed invoice field, the documented workaround is *job-linked asset + asset report*, not a native invoice field.",
