    asker: { name: "Amanda Foster", slackId: "U1022" },
    questionText: "what is the limit on how many locations a customer record can have?",
    threadContext: null,
    answerText: "I still *couldn’t find a documented numeric limit* on how many *additional locations* a single customer record can have.\n\nWhat’s confirmed:\n- You can add *additional locations* to a customer record manually, and the public docs also note multi-location setup/import support.\n- For *related customers* (parent/child), the docs explicitly say you can add *as many related customers as needed*.\n- For *multi-location customers*, neither source lists a maximum number of locations.\n\nInternal context that adds a little:\n- Confluence gives the *operational setup flow* for adding locations:\n  - Enter the *Primary Address*\n  - Select *Additional Location*\n  - Enter details and click *Save New Location*\n  - You can also attach contacts to a location via *Related Contacts*, set a primary contact for that address, and on jobs the *Location* selection can auto-switch the *Contact* if one is tied to that address  \n  📕 Internal: <https://fieldpulse.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/FKB/pages/717914113|Multi-Location & Multi-Contact Customers>\n- But *that internal page also does not state any hard cap*.\n\nSo the best internal answer is:\n- *No documented system limit found* for locations on one customer record.\n- The docs support the feature, but neither Help Center nor Confluence gives a max-count value.  \n  📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/customers/character-limits|Customer Record: FieldPulse Character Limits and Validation Rules>  \n  📘 Help Center: <https://fieldpulse.mintlify.app/core-platform/customers/multi-location|Multi-Location & Related Customers>  \n  📕 Internal: <https://fieldpulse.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/FKB/pages/717914113|Multi-Location & Multi-Contact Customers>\n\n*Net: Confluence doesn’t add a numeric limit beyond the Help Center baseline.* If someone needs an exact hard cap, this still has to be confirmed with Support/Engineering.",
